{{unreferenced|date=March 2010}}
{{Infobox journal | title = Early Theatre | cover =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Early theatre.jpg]] --> | editor = Helen Ostovich | discipline = [[Drama|Dramatic arts]] | formernames = REED Newsletter | frequency = Biannually | abbreviation = Early Theatre | impact = | impact-year = | publisher = [[Centre for Reformation and Renaissance Studies]] | country = Canada | history = 1998-present | website = http://digitalcommons.mcmaster.ca/earlytheatre/ | link1 = | link1-name = | JSTOR = | ISSN = 1206-9078 | eISSN = | OCLC = 40564695 | LCCN = }} '''''Early Theatre''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] specialising in the study of [[medieval theatre|medieval]] and early modern [[drama|theatre and drama]], particularly in England, Scotland, Ireland, and Wales. The journal originally evolved out of the ''REED Newsletter'', which was published biannually by the Records of Early English Drama, and the first issue was published in 1998. It is edited by Helen Ostovich.
== External links == * {{Official website|http://digitalcommons.mcmaster.ca/earlytheatre/}}
